    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.36.12-13_0001a" />
                 
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                Skryim Farm,<lb/>
                Route 7<lb/>
                Columbia, Mo.<lb/>
                
                4-27-62
                    </dateline>
                
                
                <salute>Dear Mrs. Weaver<lb/>
                and<lb/>
                Russel Moran:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I'm very sorry that I can't help you with the totem pole. <hi rend="underline">My</hi> Indians are of the Plains &#8212; chiefly the Sioux &#8212; and we don't carve totem poles. I would suggest that you write to the <address><addrLine>Director of Information,</addrLine> <addrLine>The Indian Bureau,</addrLine>
                
                <note type="authorial">(over)</note>
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.36.12-13_0001b"/>
                    <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
                   
                
                <addrLine>Dep't. of the Interior,</addrLine>
                    <addrLine>Washington 25</addrLine>
                    <addrLine><hi rend="caps">D. C.</hi>.</addrLine> 
                    </address>
                    <fw type="curatorial"><del/></fw>
                    
                    You might say that I suggested your writing. I was for several years the Dir. of Information under John Collier and Mr. Brophy. Perhaps I am not <hi rend="underline">quite</hi> forgotten there.</p>
               
                <p><hi rend="triple underline">But</hi>, my whole heart is with you. I want to help. <note type="authorial">(inside)</note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">12</fw>
                    <pb facs="nei.j4c.36.12-13_0002"/>
                <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
                    
                The enclosed check merely signifies my desire to help. How much is needed?</p>
                
                <p>Yes, Slade Kendrick <hi rend="italic">is tops</hi> in every way. Bless his heart!</p>
                <closer>
                <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                <signed>John Neihardt</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <fw type="curatorial"><del/></fw>
                <fw type="curatorial">13</fw>
            </div1>
        </body>
        
